obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (46519)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46519&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the Northern India Canal and Drainage Act, 1873.`
  line
  line `Local extent.--It extends to ^1[Uttar Pradesh and the ^2[territories which, immediately before`
  line `the 1st November, 1956, were comprised in the States of Punjab and Delhi]] and applies to all`
  line `lands whether permanently settled, temporarily settled, or free from revenue.`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O.1948, for the original words as amended by the A.O.1937. The Act originally extended to the`
  line `territories which are now the U.P., the Punjab, and the C.P. It has been rep. in the C.P. by the C.P. Irrigation Act,`
  line `1931 (C.P. 3 of 1931). It has been declared not to apply to any canal which is included for the time being under`
  line `Sch. I or Sch. II to the Punjab Minor Canals Act, 1905 (Pun. 3 of 1905), see s. 2 (3) of that Act. The Act has been`
  line `amended and in Punjab by Pun. Acts 19 of 1953, 22 of 1960 and 18 of 1974`
  line `in U.P. by U.P. Acts 30 of 1956 and`
  line `16 of 1974; and in Haryana by Haryana Acts 4 of 1971 and 29 of 1974.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order, 1956, for "States of Punjab and Delhi".`
  line
  line `3. The commencement paragraph rep. by Act 16 of 1874, s. 1 and Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (46520)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title [Repealed.].
  content `[Repeal of Acts.] Rep. by the Repealing Act, 1873 (12 of 1873), s. 1 and Schedule.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46520&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (46521)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Interpretation clause.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46521&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there be something repugnant in the subject or`
  line `context:--`
  line
  line `(1) Canal.--canal includes--`
  line
  line `(a) all canals, channels and reservoirs constructed, maintained or controlled by the State`
  line `Government for the supply or storage of water;`
  line
  line `(b) all works, embankments, structures, supply and escape channels connected with such`
  line `canals, channels or reservoirs;`
  line
  line `(c) all water-courses as defined in the second clause of this section;`
  line
  line `(d) any part of a river, stream, lake or natural collection of water, or natural`
  line `drainage-channel, to which the State Government has applied the provisions of Part`
  line `II of this Act;`
  line
  line `(2) Water course.--water course means any channel which is supplied with water`
  line `from a canal, but which is not maintained at the cost of the State Government, and all`
  line `subsidiary works belonging to any such channel;`
  line
  line `(3) Drainage-work.--drainage-work includes escape-channels from a canal, dams,`
  line `weirs, embankments, sluices, groins and other works for the protection of lands from flood or`
  line `from erosion, formed or maintained by the State Government under the provisions of Part VII`
  line `of this Act, but does not include works for the removal of sewage from towns;`
  line
  line `^1(4) Vessel.--vessel includes boats, rafts, timber and other floating bodies;`
  line
  line `(5) Commissioner.--Commissioner means a Commissioner of a division, and includes any`
  line `officer appointed under this Act to exercise all or any of the powers of a Commissioner;`
  line
  line `^2(6) Collector.--Collector means the head revenue-officer of a district, and includes a`
  line `Deputy Commissioner or other officer appointed under this Act to exercise all or any of the powers of`
  line `a Collector;`
  line
  line `(7) Canal-officer.--Canal-officer means an officer appointed under this Act to exercise`
  line `control or jurisdiction over a canal or any part thereof;`
  line
  line `Superintending Canal-officer.--Superintending Canal-officer means an officer exercising`
  line `general control over a canal or portion of a canal;`
  line
  line `Divisional Canal-officer.--Divisional Canal-officer means an officer exercising control`
  line `over a division of a canal;`
  line
  line `Sub-divisional Canal-officer.--Sub-Divisional Canal-officer means an officer exercising`
  line `control over a sub-division of a canal;`
  line
  line `(8) District.--District means a district as fixed for revenue purposes.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 3 of Act no. VIII of 1873.— In clause (8) of section 3 of the Northern India Canal and Drainage Act, 1873 (hereinafter called the principal Act) for the full stop a semi-colon shall be substituted and thereafter the following shall be added as new clauses (9) and (10) ;`
  line
  line `“(9) ‘irrigable command area’ means such area of culturable land or grove land which, for purposes of irrigation, can be commanded through a single outlet in a canal or by a single tube-well and the limits of which are fixed in this behalf by the Divisional Canal Officer ; and`
  line
  line `(10) ‘Prescribed’ means prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act V of 1963, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Cf. definition in the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897), s. 3.`
  line
  line `2. Cf. definition in the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897), s. 3 (11).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (46522)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Power to appoint officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46522&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may from time to time declare, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, the officers by whom, and the local limits within which, all or any of the powers`
  line `or duties hereinafter conferred or imposed shall be exercised or performed.`
  line
  line `All officers mentioned in section 3, clause (7), shall be respectively subject to the orders of such`
  line `officers as the State Government from time to time directs.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 4 of Act no. XVII of 1878.—In the first proviso to section 4 of the Northern India Ferries Act, 1878, as amend in its application to Uttar Pradesh, between the words “two States” and the words “the powers”, the words “to which this Act applies” shall be inserted.`
  line
  line `[Vide@ Uttar Pradesh Act IV of 1960, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (46523)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Notification to issue when water-supply is to be applied for public purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46523&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Whenever it`
  line `appears expedient to the State Government that the water of any river or stream flowing in a natural`
  line `channel, or of any lake or other natural collection of still water, should be applied or used by the State`
  line `Government for the purpose of any existing or projected canal or drainage-work, the State Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare that the said water will be so applied or used after a`
  line `day to be named in the said notification, not being earlier than three months from the date thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (46524)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Powers of Canal-officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46524&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `At any time after the day so named, any Canal-officer, acting under the`
  line `orders of the State Government in this behalf, may enter on any land and remove any obstructions, and`
  line `may close any channels, and do any other thing necessary for such application or use of the said water.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (46525)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Notice as to claims for compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46525&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `As soon as is practicable after the issue of such`
  line `notification, the Collector shall cause public notice to be given at convenient places, stating that the State`
  line `Government intends to apply or use the said water as aforesaid, and that claims for compensation in`
  line `respect of the matters mentioned in section 8 may be made before him.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (46526)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Damage for which compensation shall not be awarded.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Indian Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46526&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `No compensation shall be awarded for`
  line `any damage caused by--`
  line
  line `(a) stoppage or diminution of percolation or floods;`
  line
  line `(b) deterioration of climate or soil;`
  line
  line `(c) stoppage of navigation, or of the means of drifting timber or watering cattle;`
  line
  line `(d) displacement of labour.`
  line
  line `Matters in respect of which compensation may be awarded.--But compensation may be awarded`
  line `in respect of any of the following matters:--`
  line
  line `(e) stoppage or diminution of supply of water through any natural channel to any defined`
  line `artificial channel, whether above or underground, in use at the date of the said notification;`
  line
  line `(f) stoppage or diminution of supply of water to any work erected for purposes of profit on any`
  line `channel, whether natural or artificial, in use at the date of the said notification;`
  line
  line `(g) stoppage or diminution of supply of water through any natural channel which has been`
  line `used for purposes of irrigation within the five years next before the date of the said notification;`
  line
  line `(h) damage done in respect of any right to a water-course or the use of any water to which any`
  line `person is entitled under the ^1Indian Limitation Act, 1877 (15 of 1877), Part IV;`
  line
  line `(i) any other substantial damage, not falling under any of the above clauses (a), (b), (c) or`
  line `(d), and caused by the exercise of the powers conferred by this Act, which is capable of being`
  line `ascertained and estimated at the time of awarding such compensation.`
  line
  line `In determining the amount of such compensation, regard shall be had to the diminution`
  line `in the market-value, at the time of awarding compensation of the property in respect of`
  line `which compensation is claimed; and, where such market-value is not ascertainable, the`
  line `amount shall be reckoned at twelve times the amount of the diminution of the annual net`
  line `profits of such property caused by the exercise of the powers conferred by this Act.`
  line
  line `No right to any such supply of water as is referred to in clauses (e), (f) or (g) of this`
  line `section, in respect of a work or channel not in use at the date of the notification, shall be`
  line `acquired as against the State Government, except by grant or under the ^1Indian Limitation`
  line `Act, 1877 (15 of 1877), Part IV;`
  line
  line `and no right to any of the advantages referred to in clauses (a), (b) and (c) of this section shall be`
  line `acquired, as against the State Government, under the same Part.`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (46527)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Limitation of claims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46527&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `No claim for compensation for any such stoppage, diminution`
  line `or damage shall be made after the expiration of one year from such stoppage, diminution or`
  line `damage, unless the Collector is satisfied that the claimant had sufficient cause for not making`
  line `the claim within such period`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (46528)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Enquiry into claims and amount of compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Land Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of 1894).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46528&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The Collector shall proceed to`
  line `enquire into any such claim, and to determine the amount of compensation, if any, which should`
  line `be given to the claimant; and sections 9 to 12 (inclusive), 14 and 15, 18 to 23 (inclusive), 26 to`
  line `40 (inclusive), 51, 57, 58 and 59 of the ^1Land Acquisition Act, 1870 (10 of 1870), shall apply to`
  line `such inquiries:`
  line
  line `Provided that, instead of the last clause of the said section 26, the following shall be`
  line `read:-- "The provisions of this section and of section 8 of the Northern India Canal and`
  line `Drainage Act, 1873 (8 of 1873), shall be read to every assessor in a language which he`
  line `understands, before he gives his opinion as to the amount of compensation to be`
  line `awarded."`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (46529)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Abatement of rent on interruption of water-supply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46529&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Every tenant holding under`
  line `an unexpired lease, or having a right of occupancy, who is in occupation of any land at the`
  line `time when any stoppage or diminution of water-supply, in respect of which compensation`
  line `is allowed under section 8, takes place, may claim an abatement of the r ent previously`
  line `payable by him for the said land, on the ground that the interruption reduces the value of`
  line `the holding.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 11 of Act XVII of 1878.— In section 11 of the Northern India Ferries Act, 1878, for the words “one month’s thin” the word “three months” shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act XXIX of 1948, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (46530)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Enhancement of rent on restoration of water-supply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46530&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `If a water-supply increasing the value`
  line `of such holding is afterwards restored to the said land, the rent of the tenant may be enhanced in respect`
  line `of the increased value of such land due to the restored water-supply, to an amount not exceeding that at`
  line `which it stood immediately before the abatement.`
  line
  line `Such enhancement shall be on account only of the restored water-supply, and shall not`
  line `affect the liability of the tenant to enhancement of rent on any other grounds.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (46531)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Compensation when due.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46531&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `All sums of money payable for compensation under this`
  line `Part shall become due three months after the claim for such compensation is made in`
  line `respect of the stoppage, diminution or damage complained of,`
  line
  line `Interest.--and simple interest at the rate of six per cent. per annum shall be allowed on any`
  line `such sum remaining unpaid after the said three months, except where the non-payment of such`
  line `sum is caused by the wilful neglect or refusal of the claimant to receive the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (46532)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Power to enter and survey, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46532&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Any Canal-officer, or other person acting under the general or`
  line `special order of a Canal-officer,`
  line
  line `may enter upon any lands adjacent to any canal, or through which any canal is`
  line `proposed to be made, and undertake surveys or levels thereon;`
  line
  line `and dig and bore into the sub-soil;`
  line
  line `and make and set upsuitable land-marks, level-marks and watergauges;`
  line
  line `and do all other acts necessary for the proper prosecution of any enquiry relating to any`
  line `existing or projected canal under the charge of the said Canal-officer;`
  line
  line `Power to clear land.-- and, where otherwise such enquiry cannot be completed, such`
  line `officer or other person may cut down and clear away any part of any standing crop, fence`
  line `or jungle;`
  line
  line `Power to inspect and regulate water-supply.--And may also enter upon any land,`
  line `building or water-course on account of which any water-rate is chargeable, for the purpose`
  line `of inspecting or regulating the use of the water supplied, or of measuring the lands`
  line `irrigated thereby or chargeable with a water-rate, and of doing all things necessary for the`
  line `proper regulation and management of such canal:`
  line
  line `Notice of intended entry into houses.--Provided that, if such Canal-officer or`
  line `person proposes to enter into any building or enclosed court or garden attached to a`
  line `dwelling-house not supplied with water flowing from any canal, he shall previously give`
  line `the occupier of such building, court or garden at least seven days notice in writing of`
  line `his intention to do so.`
  line
  line `Compensation for damage caused by entry.--In every case of entry under this section, the Canalofficer shall, at the time of such entry, tender compensation for any damage which may be occasioned by`
  line `any proceeding under this section; and, in case of dispute as to the sufficiency of the amount so tendered,`
  line `he shall forthwith refer the same for decision by the Collector, and such decision shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (46533)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Power to enter for repairs and to prevent accidents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Land Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of 1894).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46533&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `In case of any accident happening or`
  line `being apprehended to a canal any Divisional Canal-officer or any person acting under his general or`
  line `special orders in this behalf may enter upon any lands adjacent to such canal, and may execute all works`
  line `which may be necessary for the purpose of repairing or preventing such accident.`
  line
  line `Compensation for damage to land.--In every such case such Canal-officer or person`
  line `shall tender compensation to the proprietors or occupiers of the said lands for all damage`
  line `done to the same. If such tender is not accepted, the Canal-officer shall refer the matter to`
  line `the Collector, who shall proceed to award compensation for the damage as though the State Government had directed the occupation of the lands under section 43 of the ^1Land Acquisition Act, 1870 (10 of 1870).`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (46534)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Application by persons desiring to use canal-water.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46534&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Any persons desiring to use the water of`
  line `any canal may apply in writing to the Divisional or Sub-Divisional Canal-officer of the division or subdivision of the canal from which the water course is to be supplied, requesting such officer to construct or`
  line `improve a water-course at the cost of the applicants.`
  line
  line `Contents of application.--The application shall state the works to be undertaken, their approximate`
  line `estimated cost, or the amount which the applicants are willing to pay for the same, or whether they`
  line `engage to pay the actual cost as settled by the Divisional Canal-officer, and how the payment is to be`
  line made.
  line
  line `Liability of applicants for cost of works.--When the assent of the Superintending Canal-officer is`
  line `given to such application, all the applicants shall, after the application has been duly attested before the`
  line `Collector, be jointly and severally liable for the cost of such works to the extent mentioned therein.`
  line
  line `Recovery of amount due.--Any amount becoming due under the terms of such application, and not`
  line `paid to the Divisional Canal-officer, or the person authorised by him to receive the same, on or before the`
  line `date on which it becomes due, shall, on the demand of such officer, be recoverable by the Collector as if it`
  line `were an arrear of land-revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (46535)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Government to provide means of crossing canals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46535&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `There shall be provided, at the cost of the`
  line `State Government, suitable means of crossing canals constructed or maintained at the cost of the State`
  line `Government, at such places as the State Government thinks necessary for the reasonable convenience of`
  line `the inhabitants of the adjacent lands.`
  line
  line `On receiving a statement in writing, signed by not less than five of the owners of such lands, to the`
  line `effect that suitable crossings have not been provided on any canal, the Collector shall cause enquiry to be`
  line `made into the circumstances of the case and if he thinks that the statement is established, he shall report`
  line `his opinion thereon for the consideration of the State Government, and the State Government shall cause`
  line `such measures in reference thereto to be taken as it thinks proper.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (46536)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Persons using water-course to construct works for passing water across roads, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46536&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line The
  line `Divisional Canal-officer may issue an order to the persons using any water-course to construct suitable`
  line `bridges, culverts or other works for the passage of the water of such water-course across any public road,`
  line `canal or drainage-channel in use before the said watercourse was made, or to repair any such works.`
  line
  line `Such order shall specify a reasonable period within which such construction or repairs shall be`
  line completed;
  line
  line `If they fail, Canal-officer may construct,-- and if, after the receipt of such order, the persons to`
  line `whom it is addressed do not, within the said period, construct or repair such works to the satisfaction of`
  line `the said Canal-officer, he may, with the previous approval of the Superintending Canal-officer, himself`
  line `construct or repair the same;`
  line
  line `and recover cost,-- and if the said persons do not, when so required, pay the cost of such`
  line `construction or repairs as declared by the Divisional Canal-officer, the amount shall, on the demand of the`
  line `Divisional Canal-officer, be recoverable from them by the Collector as if it were an arrear of landrevenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (46537)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Adjustment of claims between persons jointly using water-course.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46537&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `If any person, jointly`
  line `responsible with others for the construction or maintenance of a water-course, or jointly making use of a`
  line `water-course with others, neglects or refuses to pay his share of the cost of such construction or`
  line `maintenance, or to execute his share of any work necessary for such construction or maintenance, the`
  line `Divisional or Sub-divisional Canal-officer, on receiving an application in writing from any person injured`
  line `by such neglect or refusal, shall serve notice on all the parties concerned that, on the expiration of a fortnight from the service, he will investigate the case; and shall, on the expiration of that period,`
  line `investigate the case accordingly, and make such order thereon as to him seems fit.`
  line
  line `Such order shall be appealable to the Commissioner, whose order thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `Recovery of amount found due.--Any sum directed by such order to be paid within a`
  line `specified period may, if not paid within such period, and if the order remains in force, be`
  line `recovered by the Collector, from the person directed to pay the same, as if it were an`
  line `arrear of land-revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (46538)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Supply of water through intervening wafer-course.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46538&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Whenever application is`
  line `made to a Divisional Canal-officer for a supply of water from a canal, and it appears to him`
  line `expedient that such supply should be given and that it should be conveyed through some`
  line `existing water-course, he shall give notice to the persons responsible for the maintenance`
  line `of such water-course to show cause, on a day not less than fourteen days from the date of`
  line `such notice, why the said supply should not be so conveyed; and, after making enquiry on`
  line `such day, the Divisional Canal-officer shall determine whether and on what conditions the`
  line `said supply shall be conveyed through such water-course.`
  line
  line `When such officer determines that a supply of canal-water may be conveyed through`
  line `any water-course as aforesaid, his decision shall, when confirmed or modified by the`
  line `Superintending Canal-officer, be binding on the applicant and also on the persons`
  line `responsible for the maintenance of the said water-course.`
  line
  line `Such applicant shall not be entitled to use such water-course until he has paid the`
  line `expense of any alteration of such water-course necessary in order to his being supplied`
  line `through it, and also such share of the first cost of such water-course as the Divisional or`
  line `Superintending Canal-officer may determine.`
  line
  line `Such applicant shall also be liable for his share of the cost of maintenance of such`
  line `water-course so long as he uses it.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (46539)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Application for construction of new water-course.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46539&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Any person desiring the construction of`
  line `new water-course may apply in writing to the Divisional Canal-officer, stating--`
  line
  line `(1) that he has endeavoured unsuccessfully to acquire, from the owners of the land`
  line `through which he desires such water-course to pass, a right to occupy so much of the`
  line `land as will be needed for such water-course;`
  line
  line `(2) that he desires the said Canal-officer, in his behalf and at his cost, to do all things necessary`
  line `for acquiring such right;`
  line
  line `(3) that he is able to defray all costs involved in acquiring such right and constructing such`
  line water-course.
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (46540)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Procedure of Canal-officer thereupon.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46540&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `If the Divisional Canal-officer considers--`
  line
  line `(1) that the construction of such water-course is expedient, and`
  line
  line `(2) that the statements in the application are true,`
  line
  line `he shall call upon the applicant to make such deposit as the Divisional Canal-officer considers necessary`
  line `to defray the cost of the preliminary proceedings, and the amount of any compensation which he`
  line `considers likely to become due under section 28;`
  line
  line `and, upon such deposit being made, he shall cause enquiry to be made into the most suitable`
  line `alignment for the said water-course, and shall mark out the land which, in his opinion, it will be,`
  line `necessary to occupy for the construction thereof, and shall forthwith publish a notice in every village`
  line `through which the water-course is proposed to be taken, that so much of such land as belongs to such`
  line `village has been so marked out, and shall send a copy of such notice to the Collector of every district in`
  line `which any part of such land is situate.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (46541)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Application for transfer of existing water-course.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46541&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Any person desiring that an existing watercourse should be transferred from its present owner to himself may apply in writing to the Divisional`
  line `Canal-officer, stating--`
  line
  line `(1) that he has endeavoured unsuccessfully to procure such transfer from the owner of such`
  line water-course;
  line
  line `(2) that he desires the said Canal-officer, in his behalf and at his cost, to do all things necessary`
  line `for procuring such transfer;`
  line
  line `(3) that he is able to defray the cost of such transfer.`
  line
  line `Procedure thereupon.--If the Divisional Canal-officer considers--`
  line
  line `(a) that the said transfer is necessary for the better Management of the irrigation from such`
  line `water-course, and`
  line
  line `(b) that the statements in the application are true,`
  line
  line `he shall call upon the applicant to make such deposit as the Divisional Canal-officer considers necessary`
  line `to defray the cost of the preliminary proceedings, and the amount of any compensation that may become`
  line `due under the provisions of section 28 in respect of such transfer; and upon such deposit being made, he`
  line `shall publish a notice of the application in every village, and shall send a copy of the notice to the`
  line `Collector of every district, through which such water-course passes.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (46542)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Objections to construction or transfer applied for.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46542&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Within thirty days from the publication of`
  line `a notice under section 22 or section 23, as the case may be, any person interested in the land or watercourse to which the notice refers may apply to the Collector by petition stating his objection to the`
  line `construction or transfer for which application has been made.`
  line
  line `The Collector may either reject the petition or may proceed to inquire into the validity of the`
  line `objection, giving previous notice to the Divisional Canal-officer of the place and time at which such`
  line `inquiry will be held.`
  line
  line `The Collector shall record in writing all orders passed by him under this section and the grounds`
  line thereof.
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (46543)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `When applicant may be placed in occupation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46543&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `If no such objection is made, or (where such`
  line `objection is made) if the Collector over-rules it, he shall give notice to the Divisional Canal-officer to that`
  line `effect, and shall proceed forthwith to place the said applicant in occupation of the land marked out or of`
  line `the water-course to be transferred, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (46544)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Procedure when objection is held valid.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46544&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `If the Collector considers any objection made as`
  line `aforesaid to be valid he shall inform the Divisional Canal-officer accordingly; and, if such officer sees fit,`
  line `he may, in the case of an application under section 21, alter the boundaries of the land so marked out, and`
  line `may give fresh notice under section 22; and the procedure herein before provided shall be applicable to`
  line `such notice, and the Collector shall thereupon proceed as before provided.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (46545)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Procedure when Canal-officer disagrees with Collector.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46545&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `If the Canal-officer disagrees with`
  line `the Collector, the matter shall be referred for decision to the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `Such decision shall be final, and the Collector, if he is so directed by such decision, shall, subject to`
  line `the provisions of section 28, cause the said applicant to be placed in occupation of the land so marked out`
  line `or of the water-course to be transferred, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (46546)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Expenses to be paid by applicant before receiving occupation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Land Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of 1894).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46546&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `No such applicant shall be`
  line `placed in occupation of such land or water-course until he has paid to the person named by the Collector`
  line `such amount as the Collector determines to be due as compensation for the land or water-course so`
  line `occupied or transferred, and for any damage caused by the marking out or occupation of such land,`
  line `together with all expenses incidental to such occupation or transfer.`
  line `Procedure in fixing compensation.--In determining the compensation to be made under this section`
  line `the Collector shall proceed under the provisions of the Land Acquisition Act, 1870`
  line ^1
  line `(10 of 1870); but he`
  line `may, if the person to be compensated so desires, award such compensation in the form of a rent-charge`
  line `payable in respect of the land or water-course occupied or transferred.`
  line `Recovery of compensation and expenses.--If such compensation and expenses are not paid when`
  line `demanded by the person entitled to receive the same, the amount may be recovered by the Collector as if`
  line `it were any arrear of land-revenue, and shall, when recovered, be paid by him to the person entitled to`
  line `receive the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (46547)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Conditions binding on applicant placed in occupation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46547&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `When any such applicant is placed in`
  line `occupation of land or of a water-course as aforesaid, the following rules and conditions shall be binding`
  line `on him and his representative in interest :--`
  line
  line `First.--All works necessary for the passage across such water-course, of water-courses existing`
  line `previous to its construction and of the drainage intercepted by it, and for affording proper`
  line `communications across it for the convenience of the neighbouring lands, shall be constructed by the`
  line `applicant, and be maintained by him or his representative in interest to the satisfaction of the`
  line `Divisional Canal-officer.`
  line
  line `Second.--Land occupied for a water-course under the provisions of section 22 stall be used only`
  line `for the purpose of such water-course.`
  line
  line `Third.--The proposed water-course shall be completed to the satisfaction of the Divisional Canalofficer within one year after the applicant is placed in occupation of the land.`
  line `In cases in which land is occupied or a water-course is transferred on the terms of a rent-charge.`
  line
  line `Fourth.--The applicant or his representative in interest shall, so long as he occupies such land or`
  line `water-course, pay rent for the same at such rate and on such days as are determined by the Collector`
  line `when the applicant is placed in occupation.`
  line
  line `Fifth.--If the right to occupy the land cease owing to a breach of any of these rules, the liability to`
  line `pay the said rent shall continue until the applicant or his representative in interest has restored the`
  line `land to its original condition, or until he has paid, by way of compensation for any injury done to the`
  line `said land, such amount and to such persons as the Collector determines.`
  line
  line `Sixth.--The Collector may, on the application of the person entitled to receive such rent or`
  line `compensation, determine the amount of rent due or assess the amount of such compensation; and, if`
  line `any such rent or compensation be not paid by the applicant or his representative in interest, the`
  line `Collector may recover the amount, with interest thereon at the rate of six per cent. per annum from`
  line `the date on which it became due, as if it were an arrear of land-revenue, and shall pay the same, when`
  line `recovered, to the person to whom it is due.`
  line
  line `If any of the rules and conditions prescribed by this section are not complied with,`
  line
  line `or if any water-course constructed or transferred under this Act is disused for three years`
  line continuously,
  line
  line `the right of the applicant, or of his representative in interest, to occupy such land or water-course`
  line `shall cease absolutely.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (46548)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Procedure applicable to occupation for extensions and alterations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46548&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The procedure`
  line `hereinbefore provided for the occupation of land for the construction of a water-course shall be`
  line `applicable to the occupation of land for any extension or alteration of a water-course, and for`
  line `the deposit of soil from water-course clearances.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Addition of new section 30-A to 30-G in Act no. VIII of 1873.--After section 30 of the principal Act, the following shall be added as new sections 30-A to 0-G :`
  line
  line `“30-A. Preparation of the scheme for an irrigable command area.—The Divisional Canal Officer may, with a view to providing for or improving irrigation facilities in an irrigable command area, prepare a scheme for the construction of water-courses and the carrying out of any work connected therewith in such area, anything to the contrary contained in any other law notwithstanding. The scheme shall contain —`
  line
  line `(i) a plan showing the site of the outlet, the existing water-courses, if any, the proposed water-courses and works connected therewith, and the areas already served and to be served by the existing or proposed watercourses;`
  line
  line `(ii) a statement showing the estimated cost of constructing the proposed water-courses and works connected therewith ;`
  line
  line `(iii) a memorandum showing the manner in which the scheme may be implemented; and`
  line `(iv) such other particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `30-B. Calling upon the Gaon Sabhas to implement the scheme.—(1) The Divisional Canal Officer shall, as soon as may be, forward a copy of the scheme prepared under section 30-A to each of the Gaon Sabhas and Block Development Officers within whose jurisdiction the land affected thereby is situate, and call upon the Gaon Sabhas to submit to him within a period of thirty days from the date of receipt of the copy, their approval or the scheme, or any objections, suggestions or modifications thereto.`
  line
  line `(2) The copy of the scheme shall, within three days of its receipt by the Gaon Sabha, be affixed by it on its notice board, and shall, within twelve days thereafter, be considered in a meeting of the Gaon Panchayat convened for the purpose and the decision of the Gaon Panchayat shall be deemed tobe for and on behalf of the Gaon Sabha concerned. The decision shall be communicated to the Divisional Canal Officer within the time allowed under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) If no objections, modifications or suggestions are submitted by any of the Gaon Sabhas within the time specified in sub-section (1), the Gaon Sabhas shall be deemed to have approved the scheme, which shall thereupon become final.`
  line
  line `(4) Upon receipt of the objections, modifications or suggestions, made by the Gaon Sabhas under sub-section (2), the Divisional Canal Officer may either confirm the scheme or amend or modify it and thereupon the scheme so confirmed, amended or modified, shall become final.`
  line
  line `(5) When the scheme has become final, the Divisional Canal Officer shall, by notice in writing, call upon the Gaon Sabhas concerned to take all such steps as may be necessary for the implementation of the scheme, and in particular to construct or cause to be constructed, the water-courses and carry out, or cause to be carried out, all works connected therewith, within the period fixed therefor in the notice, which may be extended from time to time.`
  line
  line `30-C. Securing or acquiring land for the scheme.—(1) Upon receipt of the notice mentioned in sub-section (5) of section 30-B, the Gaon Sabha shall give to all persons on whose land any water-course is proposed to be constructed, or on which any work connected therewith is proposed to be carried out, option to transfer by way of gift or surrender, as the case may be, free from all encumbrances, within the period provided therefor in the notice, so much of the said land in its favour as may be necessary for the implementation of the scheme.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any land required for the implementation of the scheme is not transferred to, or surrendered in favour of the Gaon Sabha under subsection (1), it may —`
  line
  line `(i) either purchase the land at such rates as may be prescribed ; or`
  line
  line `(ii) move the State Government to acquire the same under the Land Acquisition Act, 1894 (Act no. 1 of 1894) ; or`
  line
  line `(iii) If the land for construction of water-courses is likely to be required for a limited period only, apply to the Requisitioning Authority under section 6 of U. P. Rural Development (Requisitioning of Land) Act, 1948 (U.P. Act no XXVII of 1948) to requisition the land ;`
  line
  line `Provided that if it appears after the construction of water-courses on the land so requisitioned that the alignment of the water-courses as constructed will be retained unchanged for long the Gaon Sabha shall, as early as possible, move the State Government to acquire the land on a permanent basis.`
  line
  line `(3) Where, on the application of the Gaon Sabha under sub-section (2), any land has been acquired in accordance with the provisions of the Land Acquisition Act, 1894 (Act no. 1 of 1894), the State Government shall, subject to such terms and conditions as may be imposed by it in this behalf, transfer to, or vest in, the Gaon Sabha, the land so acquired for the implementation of the scheme.`
  line
  line `(4) The land transferred to, or vested in, the Gaon Sabha under subsection (3), or of which the management has been vested in the Gaon Sabha under section 11 of the U. P. Rural Development (Requisitioning of Land) Act, 1948 (U.P. Act no. XXVII of 1948), shall be utilized by the Gaon Sabha for the implementation of the scheme, and it shall construct or cause to be constructed, in the manner hereinafter provided, the water-courses, and carry out or cause to be carried out, all works connected therewith as may be necessary for the implementation of the scheme.`
  line
  line `(5) In implementing the scheme the Gaon Sabha shall, in the first instance, give option, by notice in writing, published the manner prescribed, to all persons having a holding in the irrigable command area, to construct, within such time as may be fixed therefor in the notice, the water courses, and carry out all such work connected therewith, as may be necessary for the implementation of the scheme.`
  line
  line `(6) Where the persons concerned fail to construct the whole or any part of any water-course, or to carry out any work connected therewith, in accordance with the scheme, the Gaon Sabha shall construct, or carry out, or cause to be constructed, or carried out, the same in the manner provided under section 17 of the Uttar Pradesh Panchayat Raj Act, 1947, for the execution of small Irrigation projects.`
  line
  line `30-D. Inspection of work by the Divisional Canal Officer.—(1) On the expiry of the period or extended period, as the case may be, specified in the notice under sub-section (5) of section 30-B, the Divisional Canal Officer shall inspect, or cause to be inspected, the water courses and all works connected therewith, constructed or carried out, by the Gaon Sabha, either directly or through the tenure-holders of the irrigable command area, and if the same are in accordance with scheme and otherwise properly constructed, or carried out, approve the same.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the water-courses or all works connected therewith, have not been properly constructed or carried out in accordance with the scheme, the Divisional Canal Officer, shall, by order in writing, require the Gaon Sabha concerned to remove and remedy, or cause to be removed and remedied, all the defects within the period specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(3) On the expiry of the period allowed in the order under sub-section (2), the Divisional Canal Officer shall again inspect, or cause to be inspected, the water-courses, and all works connected therewith, and shall either approve or dis-approve the same.`
  line
  line `30-E.Implementation of the scheme by the State Government.--Where the Gaon Sabha fails —`
  line
  line `(i) to take all or any of the steps required to be taken by it in accordance with the provisions of section 30-C ; or`
  line
  line `(ii) to construct, or cause to be constructed, the whole of the watercourses, or to carry out all works connected therewith, in accordance with the scheme, within the period or the extended period provided therefor in the notice under sub-section (5) of section 30-B ; or`
  line
  line `(iii) to remove the defects in the water-courses or in any work connected therewith as required to be done under sub-section (2) of section 30-D, or to obtain final approval of the Divisional Canal Officer in respect of them under sub-section (3) of the said section ;`
  line
  line `the State Government shall take all such steps, including acquisition of the land, as may be necessary for the implementation of the scheme, and cause to be constructed and carried out the water-courses and all works connected therewith in accordance with the scheme.`
  line
  line `30-F.Vesting of water-courses etc. in the Gaon Sabha.—With effect from the date a notification in this behalf is published in the Gazette by the State Government, and subject to such terms and conditions as may be prescribed, all the water-courses and all works carried out by the State Government in connection with the implementation of the scheme, shall vest in the Gaon Sabha within whose jurisdiction the same lie.`
  line
  line `30-G. Maintenance of the watercourses, etc.—The Gaon Sabha shall at all times maintain and keep in good repairs all the water-courses, and all the works connected therewith, constructed or carried out by it, or vested in it under section 30-F.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act V of 1963, s. 3]`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 30-EE is Act no. 8 of 1873./— After section 30-E of the Northern India Canal and rainage Act, 1873, amended in its application to Uttar Pradesh, the following section shall be inserted, namely :—`
  line
  line `“30-EE. Special provisions in respect of major irrigation projects.—(1) In any area covered by the Command of the Gandak, the Sharda Sahayak or the Ram Ganga Irrigation Project or any other major project specified in this behalf by the State Government by notification in the Gazette, the Divisional Canal Officer of the Irrigation Division may prepare a scheme containing the particulars referred to in section 30-A, and hereupon he may take all such steps as may be necessary for the implementation of the scheme, and cause to be constructed and carried out water-courses and all works connected therewith in accordance with the scheme, and nothing in sections 30-B, 30-C, 30-D and 30-E, shall apply in relation to such scheme.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), the Divisional Canal Officer may —`
  line
  line `(a) apply to the requisitioning authority under the U. P. Rural Development (Requisitioning of Land) Act, 1948, to requisition any land required for implementation of the scheme ; or`
  line `(b) move the State Government to acquire under the Land Acquisition Act, 1894, any land required for implementation of the scheme ; or`
  line
  line `(c) take action both under clauses (a) and (b), namely, to have land requisitioned in the first instance, and thereafter acquired.`
  line
  line `(3) The Divisional Canal Officer may delegate his functions under sub-section (2) to a Sub-divisional Canal Officer.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of sections 30-F, 30-G and 36-A, shall apply in relation to a scheme prepared under this section and to water-courses and other works constructed under such scheme as they apply to any scheme referred to in sections 30-A, 30-B, 30-C, 30-D and 30-E and to water-courses and other works constructed in accordance therewith.”`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 16 of 1974, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (46549)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `In absence of written contract, water-supply to be subject to rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46549&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `In the absence`
  line `of a written contract, or so far as any such contract does not extend, every supply of canalwater shall be deemed to be given at the rates and subject to the conditions prescribed by the`
  line `rules to be made by the State Government in respect thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (46595)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Conditions as to— power to stop water-supply; claims to compensation in case of failure or stoppage of supply; claims on account of interruption from other causes; duration of supply; sale or sub-letting of right to use canal-water; transfer, with land, of contracts for water; no right acquired by user.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Indian Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46595&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Such contracts and rules must be consistent, with the following`
  line `conditions:--`
  line
  line `(a) Power to stop water-supply.--The Divisional Canal-officer may not stop the supply of`
  line `water to any water-course, or to any person, except in the following cases:`
  line
  line `(1) whenever and so long as it is necessary to stop such supply for the purpose of`
  line `executing any work ordered by competent authority and with the previous sanction of`
  line `the State Government;`
  line
  line `(2) whenever and so long as any water-course is not maintained in such proper customary`
  line `repair as to prevent the wasteful escape of water therefrom;`
  line
  line `(3) within periods fixed from time to time by the Divisional Canal-officer;`
  line
  line `(b) Claims to compensation in case of failure or stoppage of supply.-- No claim shall be`
  line `made against the State Government for compensation in respect of loss caused by the`
  line `failure or stoppage of the water in a canal, by reason of any cause beyond the control of`
  line `the State Government or of any repairs, alterations or additions to the canal, or of any`
  line `measures taken for regulating the proper flow of water therein, or for maintaining the`
  line `established course of irrigation which the Divisional Canal-officer considers necessary;`
  line `but the person suffering such loss may claim such remission of the ordinary charges`
  line `payable for the use of the water as is authorised by the State Government :`
  line
  line `(c) Claims on account of interruption from other causes.--If the supply of water to`
  line `any land irrigated from a canal be interrupted otherwise than in the manner described in the`
  line `last preceding clause, the occupier or owner of such land may present a petition for`
  line `compensation to the Collector for any loss arising from such interruption, and the Collector`
  line `may award to the petitioner reasonable compensation for such loss:`
  line
  line `(d) Duration of supply.--When the water of a canal is supplied for the irrigation of a,`
  line `single crop, the permission to use such water shall be held to continue only until that crop`
  line `comes to maturity, and to apply only to that crop; but, if it be supplied for irrigating two`
  line `or more crops to be raised on the same land within the year, such permission shall be held`
  line `to continue for one year from the commencement of the irrigation, and to apply to such`
  line `crops only as are matured within that year :`
  line
  line `(e) Sale or subletting of right to use canal-water.--Unless with the permission of the`
  line `Superintending Canal-officer, no person entitled to use the water of any canal, or any`
  line `work, building or land appertaining to any canal, shall sell or sublet or otherwise transfer`
  line `his right to such use:`
  line
  line `Provided that the former part of this clause shall not apply to the use by a cultivating`
  line `tenant of water supplied by the owner of a water-course for the irrigation of the land held`
  line `by such tenant :`
  line
  line `Transfer, with land, of contracts for water.--But all contracts made between the`
  line `State Government and the owner or occupier of any immovable property, as to the supply`
  line `of canal-water to such property, shall be transferable therewith, and shall be presumed to`
  line `have been so transferred whenever a transfer of such property takes place :`
  line
  line `(f) No right acquired by user.--No right to the use of the water of a canal shall be, or`
  line `be deemed to have been, acquired under the ^1`
  line `Indian Limitation Act, 1877 (15 of 1877), Part`
  line `IV, nor shall the State Government be bound to supply any person with water except in`
  line `accordance with the terms of a contract in writing.`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (46551)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Liability when person using unauthorisedly cannot be identified.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46551&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `If water supplied through a`
  line `water-course be used in an unauthorised manner, and if the person by whose act or neglect such use has`
  line `occurred cannot be identified,`
  line
  line `the person on whose land such water has flowed if such land has derived benefit therefrom,`
  line
  line `or if such person cannot be identified or if such land has not derived benefit therefrom, all`
  line `the persons chargeable in respect of the water supplied through such water-course, shall be`
  line `liable, or jointly liable, as the case may be, to the charges made for such use.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (46552)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Liability when water runs to waste.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46552&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `If water supplied through a water-course be`
  line `suffered to run to waste, and if, after enquiry by the Divisional Canal-officer, the person`
  line `through whose act or neglect such water was suffered to run to waste cannot be discovered, all`
  line `the persons chargeable in respect of the water supplied through such water-course shall be`
  line `jointly liable for the charges made in respect of the water so wasted.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (46553)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Charges recoverable in addition to penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46553&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `All charges for the unauthorised use or`
  line `for waste of water may be recovered in addition to any penalties incurred on account of such`
  line `use or waste.`
  line
  line `Decision of questions under sections 33 and 34.--All questions under section 33 or section`
  line `34 shall be decided by the Divisional Canal-officer, subject to an appeal to the head Revenue officer of the district, or such other appeal as may be provided under section 75.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 36 of Act no. VIII of 1873.—In section 35 of the Northern India Canal and Drainage Act, 1873, hereinafter referred to as the principal Act, for the words “shall be determined by the rules to be made by the State Government”, the words “and any other incidental charges shall be determined by the rules to be made by the State Government”, shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 22 of 1979, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (46554)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Charge on occupier for water, how determined.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 16 of 1899, s. 2.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46554&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `The rates to be charged for canalwater supplied for purposes of irrigation to the occupiers of land shall be determined by the rules`
  line `to be made by the State Government, and such occupiers as accept the water shall pay for`
  line accordingly.
  line
  line `"Occupier's rate".--A rate so charged shall be called the "occupier's rate".`
  line
  line `^1[The rules hereinbefore referred to may prescribe and determine what persons or classes of`
  line `persons are to be deemed to be occupiers for the purposes of this section, and may also determine`
  line `the several liabilities, in respect of the payment of the occupier's rate, of tenants and of persons to`
  line `whom tenants may have sublet their lands or of proprietors and of persons to whom proprietors`
  line `may have let the lands held by them in cultivating occupancy.]`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (46555)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `“Owner‟s rate”.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46555&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `In addition to the occupier's rate, a rate to be called the "owner's`
  line `rate" may be imposed according to rules to be made by the State Government, on the owners of`
  line `canal-irrigated lands, in respect of the benefit which they derive from such irrigation.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (46556)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Amount of owner‟s rate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46556&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `The owner's rate shall not exceed the sum which, under`
  line `the rules for the time being in force for the assessment of land -revenue, might be assessed on`
  line `such land on account of the increase in the annual value of produce thereof caused by the`
  line `canal irrigation. And, for the purpose of this section only, land which is permanently settled`
  line `or held free of revenue shall be considered as though it wer e temporarily settled and liable to`
  line `payment of revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (46557)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Owner‟s rate, when not chargeable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46557&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `No owner's rate shall be chargeable either on`
  line `the owner or occupier of land temporarily assessed to pay land-revenue at irrigation-rates,`
  line `during the currency of such assessment.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (46558)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `When occupier is -to pay both owner‟s rate and occupier‟s rate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes `1. Sections 40 to 43 rep. in the Punjab by the Punjab Tenancy Act, 1887 (16 of 1887), s. 3 and the Schedule.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46558&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `^140. When occupier is to pay both owner's rate and occupier’s rate.--If such land is occupied by`
  line `the owner,`
  line
  line `or if it is occupied by a tenant whose rent is not liable to enhancement on the ground that`
  line `the value of the produce of the land or the productive powers of the land has or have teen`
  line `increased by irrigation,`
  line
  line `such owner or tenant shall pay the owners rate as well as the occupiers rate.`
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (46559)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Power to make rules for apportioning owner‟s rate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes `1. Sections 40 to 43 rep. in the Punjab by the Punjab Tenancy Act, 1887 (16 of 1887), s. 3 and the Schedule.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46559&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `^141. Power to make rules for apportioning owner's rate.--In the case of a tenant with a`
  line `right of occupancy, the State Government shall have power to make rules for dividing the`
  line `owner's rate between such tenant and his landlord, proportionately to the extent of the`
  line `beneficial interest of each in the land.`
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (46560)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `When owner is to pay „owner‟s rate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes `1. Sections 40 to 43 rep. in the Punjab by the Punjab Tenancy Act, 1887 (16 of 1887), s. 3 and the Schedule.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46560&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `^142. When owner is to pay owner’s rate.--If the owner of the land is not the occupier, but has`
  line `power to enhance the rent of the occupier on the ground that the value of the produce or the productive`
  line `powers of the land has or have been increased by irrigation,`
  line
  line `or if, when the amount of a rent was fixed, the land was irrigated from the canal,`
  line
  line `the owner shall pay the owner's rate.`
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (46561)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Effect of introduction of canal-irrigation on landlord’s right to enhance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes `1. Sections 40 to 43 rep. in the Punjab by the Punjab Tenancy Act, 1887 (16 of 1887), s. 3 and the Schedule`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46561&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `^143. Effect of introduction or canal-irrigation on landlord’s right to enhance.--If a`
  line `revision of settlement is a ground for entertaining a suit, for the enhancement of rent, the`
  line `introduction of canal-irrigation into any land shall have the same effect on the landlord 's right`
  line `to re-enhance the rent of a tenant with a right of occupancy of such land, as if a revision of`
  line `settlement had taken place, under which the revenue payable in respect of such land had been`
  line increased.
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (46562)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Water-rate by whom payable, when charged on land held by several owners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46562&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `Where a water-rate is charged on land held by several joint owners, it shall be payable by the`
  line `manager or other person who receives the rents or profits of such land, and may be deducted`
  line `by him from such rents or profits before division, or may be recovered by him from the`
  line `persons liable to such rate in the manner customary in the recovery of other charges on such`
  line `rents or profits.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (46563)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Certified dues recoverable as land-revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46563&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `Any sum lawfully due under this Part,`
  line `and certified by the Divisional Canal-officer to be so due, which remains unpaid after the day`
  line `on which it becomes due, shall be recoverable by the Collector from the person liable for the`
  line `same as if it were an arrear of land-revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (46564)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Power to contract for collection of canal-dues.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46564&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `The Divisional Canal-officer or the`
  line `Collector may enter into an agreement with any person for the collection and payment to the`
  line `State Government by such person of any sum payable under this Act by a third party.`
  line
  line `When such agreement has been made, such person may recover such sum by suit as though it`
  line `were a debt due to him, or an arrear of rent due to him on account of the land, wor k or building`
  line `in respect of which such sum is payable, or for or in which the canal-water shall have been`
  line `supplied or used.`
  line
  line `If such person makes default in the payment of any sum collected by him under this section, such sum`
  line `may be recovered from him by the Collector under section 45; and, if such sum or any part of it be still due by the said third party, the sum or part so due may be recovered in like manner by the Collector from`
  line `such third party.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (46565)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Lambardars may be required to collect canal-dues.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 16 of 1899, s. 3, for "or tenants".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46565&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `The Collector may require the`
  line `lambardar, or person under engagement to pay the land-revenue of any estate, to collect and`
  line `pay any sums payable under this Act by a third party, in respect of any land or water in such`
  line estate.
  line
  line `Such sums shall be recoverable by the Collector as if they were arrears of land-revenue`
  line `due in respect of the defaulter's share in such estate;`
  line
  line `and for the purpose of collecting such sums from the subordinate zamindars, rayats, ^1[tenants or sub-tenants], such lambardar or person may exercise the powers, and shall be subject to the rules, laid down in`
  line `the law for the time being in force in respect to the collection by him of the rents of land or of shares of`
  line land-revenue.
  line
  line `The State Government shall provide--`
  line
  line `(a) for remunerating persons collecting sums under this section; or`
  line
  line `(b) for indemnifying them against expenses properly incurred by them in such`
  line `collection; or`
  line
  line `(c) for both such purposes.`
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (46566)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Fines excluded from sections 45, 46, 47.`
  content `Nothing in section 45, 46 or 47 applies to fines.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46566&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (46567)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Detainer of vessels violating rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46567&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `Any vessel entering or navigating any canal`
  line `contrary to the rules made in that behalf by the State Government, or so as to cause danger`
  line `to the canal or the other vessels therein, may be r emoved or detained, or both removed and`
  line `detained, by the Divisional Canal-officer, or by any other person duly authorised in this`
  line behalf.
  line
  line `Liability of owners of vessels causing damage.--The owner of any vessel causing`
  line `damage to a canal, or removed or detained under this section, shall be liable to pay to the`
  line `State Government such sum as the Divisional Canal-officer, with the approval of the`
  line `Superintending Canal-officer, determines to be necessary to defray the expenses of repairing`
  line `such damage or of such removal or detention, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (46568)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Recovery of fines for offences in navigating canals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46568&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `Any fine imposed under this`
  line `Act upon the owner of any vessel, or the servant or agent of such owner or other person in`
  line `charge of any vessel, for any offence in respect of the navigation of such vessel, may be`
  line `recovered either in the manner prescribed by the Code of Criminal Procedure ^1`
  line `or, if the`
  line `Magistrate imposing the fine so directs, as though it were a charge due in respect of such`
  line vessel.
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (46569)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Power to seize and detain vessel on failure to pay charges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46569&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `If any charge due`
  line `under the provisions of this Part in respect of any vessel is not paid on demand to the person`
  line `authorised to collect the same, the Divisional Canal-officer may seize and detain such vessels`
  line `and the furniture thereof, until the charge so due, together with all expenses and additional`
  line `charges arising from such seizure and detention, is paid in full.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (46570)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Power to seize cargo or goods, if charges due thereon are not paid.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46570&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `If any charge`
  line `due under the provisions of this Part in respect of any cargo or goods carried in a Government`
  line `vessel on a canal, or stored on or in lands or warehouses occupied for the purposes of a canal is not paid on demand to the person authorised to collect the same, the Divisio nal Canalofficer may seize such cargo or goods and detain them until the charge so due, together with`
  line `all expenses and additional charges arising from such seizure and detention, is paid in full.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (46571)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Procedure for recovery of such charges after seizure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46571&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `Within a reasonable time after`
  line `any seizure under section 51 or section 52, the said Canal-officer shall give notice to the owner or`
  line `person in charge of the property seized that it, or such portion of it as may be necessary, will, on a`
  line `day to be named in the notice, but not sooner than fifteen days from the date of the notice, be sold`
  line `in satisfaction of the claim on account of which such property was seized, unless the claim be`
  line `discharged before the day so named.`
  line
  line `And, if such claim be not so discharged, the said Canal-officer may, on such day, sell the property`
  line `seized or such part thereof as may be necessary to yield the amount due, together with the expenses of`
  line `such seizure and sale:`
  line
  line `Provided that no greater part of the furniture of any vessel or of any cargo or goods shall be`
  line `so sold than shall, as nearly as may be, suffice to cover the amount due in respect of such`
  line `vessel, cargo or goods.`
  line
  line `The residue of such furniture, cargo or goods, and of the proceeds of the sale, shall be made over to`
  line `the owner or person in charge of the property seized.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (46572)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Procedure in respect of vessels abandoned and goods unclaimed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46572&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `If any vessel be`
  line `found abandoned in a canal, or any cargo or goods carried in a Government vessel on a canal, or`
  line `stored on or in lands or warehouses occupied for the purposes of a canal, be left unclaimed for a`
  line `period of two months, the Divisional Canal-officer may take possession of the same.`
  line
  line `The officer so taking possession may publish a notice that, if such vessel and its contents, or such`
  line `cargo or goods, are not claimed previously to a day to be named in the notice, not sooner than thirty days`
  line `from the date of such notice, he will sell the same; and, if such vessel, contents, cargo or goods be not so`
  line `claimed, he may, at any time after the day named in the notice, proceed to sell the same.`
  line
  line `Disposal of proceeds of sale.--The said vessel and its contents, and the said cargo or goods if`
  line `unsold, or, if a sale has taken place, the proceeds of the sale, after paying all tools, charges and expenses`
  line `incurred by the Divisional Canal-officer on account of the taking possession and sale, shall be made over`
  line `to the owner of the same, when his ownership is established to the satisfaction of the Divisional Canalofficer.`
  line
  line `If the Divisional Canal-officer is doubtful to whom such property or proceeds should be made over,`
  line `he may direct the property to be sold as aforesaid, and the proceeds to be paid into the district treasury,`
  line `there to be held until the right thereto be decided by a Court of competent jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (46573)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Power to prohibit obstructions or order their removal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46573&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `Whenever it appears to the State`
  line `Government that injury to any land or the public health or public convenience has arisen or may arise`
  line `from the obstruction of any river, stream or drainage-channel, such Government may, by notification`
  line `published in the Official Gazette, prohibit, within limits to be defined in such notification, the formation`
  line `of any obstruction, or may, within such limits, order the removal or other modification of such`
  line obstruction.
  line
  line `Thereupon so much of the said river, stream or drainage -channel as is comprised within`
  line `such limits shall be held to be a drainage-work as defined in section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (46574)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Power to remove obstructions after prohibition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46574&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `The Division a Canal-officer, or`
  line `other person authorised by the State Government in that behalf, may, after such publication issue`
  line `an order to the person causing or having control over any such obstruction to remove or modify`
  line `the same within a time to be fixed in the order.`
  line
  line `If, within the time so fixed, such person does not comply with the order, the said Canal-officer may`
  line `himself remove or modify the obstruction; and if the person to whom the order was issued does not, when`
  line `called upon, pay the expenses involved in such removal or modification, such expenses shall be`
  line `recoverable by the Collector from him or his representative in interest as an arrear of land-revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (46575)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Preparation of schemes for works of improvement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46575&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `Whenever it appears to the State`
  line `Government that any drainage-works are necessary for the improvement of any lands, or for the proper`
  line `cultivation or irrigation thereof,`
  line
  line `or that protection from floods or other accumulations of water, or from erosion by a river,`
  line `is required for any lands, the State Government may cause a scheme for such drainage-works`
  line `to be drawn up and published, together with an estimate of its co st and a statement of the`
  line `proportion of such cost which the State Government proposes to defray, and a schedule of the`
  line `lands which it is proposed to make chargeable in respect of the scheme.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (46576)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Powers of persons employed on such schemes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46576&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `The persons authorised by the State`
  line `Government to draw up such scheme may exercise all or any of the powers conferred on the Canalofficers by section 14.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (46577)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Rate on lands benefited by works.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46577&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `An annual rate, in respect of such scheme, may be`
  line `charged, according to rules to be made by the State Government, on the owners of all lands`
  line `which shall, in the manner prescribed by such rules, be determined to be so chargeable.`
  line
  line `Such rate shall be fixed, as nearly as possible, so as not to exceed either of the following`
  line `limits :--`
  line
  line `(1) six per cent. per annum on the first cost of the said works, adding thereto the`
  line `estimated yearly cost of the maintenance and supervision of the same, and deducting`
  line `therefrom the estimated income, if any, derived from the works, excluding the said rate:`
  line
  line `(2) in the case of agricultural land, the sum which under the rules then in force fo r the`
  line `assessment of land-revenue, might be assessed on such land on account of the increase of`
  line `the annual value or produce thereof caused by the drainage -work.`
  line
  line `Such rate may be varied from time to time, within such maximum, by the State Government.`
  line
  line `So far as any defect to be remedied is due to any canal, water-course, road or other`
  line `work or obstruction, constructed or caused by the State Government or by any person, a`
  line `proportionate share of the cost of the drainage -works required for the remedy of the said`
  line `defect shall be borne by such Government or such person, as th e case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (46578)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Recovery of rate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46578&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `Any such drainage-rate may be collected and recovered in manner provided`
  line `by sections 45, 46 and 47 for the collection and recovery of water-rates.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (46579)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Disposal of claims to compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46579&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `Whenever, in pursuance of a notification made under`
  line `section 55, any obstruction is removed or modified,`
  line
  line `or whenever any drainage-work is carried under section 57,`
  line
  line `all claims for compensation on account of any loss consequent on the removal or`
  line `modification of the said obstruction or the construction of such work may be made before the`
  line `Collector, and he shall deal with the same in the manner provided in section 10.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (46580)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Limitation of such claims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46580&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `No such claim shall be entertained after the expiration of`
  line `one year from the occurrence of the loss complained of, unless the Collector is satisfied that the`
  line `claimant had sufficient cause for not making the claim within such period.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (46581)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Definition of “labourer”.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46581&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes referred to in this Part, the word`
  line `"labourer" includes persons who exercise any handicraft specified in rules to be made in that`
  line `behalf by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (46582)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Power to prescribe number of labourers to be supplied by persons benefited by canal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46582&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line In
  line `any district in which a canal or drainage-work is constructed, maintained or projected by the State`
  line `Government, the State Government, may, if it thinks fit, direct the Collector --`
  line
  line `(a) to ascertain the proprietors, sub-proprietors or farmers whose villages or estates are`
  line `or will be in the judgment of the Collector, benefited by such canal or drainage -work, and`
  line
  line `(b) to set down in a list, having due regard to the circumstances of the districts and of`
  line `the several proprietors, sub-proprietors or farmers, the number of labourers which shall be`
  line `furnished by any of the said persons, jointly or severally, from any such village or estate,`
  line `for employment on any such canal or drainage-work when required as hereinafter`
  line provided.
  line
  line `The Collector may, from time to time, add to or alter such list or any part thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (46583)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Procedure for obtaining labour for works urgently required.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes `1. The words "with the previous sanction of the G. G. in C." omitted by Act 4 of 1914, s. 2 and the Schedule.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46583&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `Whenever it appears to a`
  line `Divisional Canal-officer duly authorised by the State Government that, unless some work is immediately`
  line `executed, such serious damage will happen to any canal or drainage-work as to cause sudden and`
  line `extensive public injury,`
  line
  line `and that the labourers necessary for the proper execution thereof cannot be obtained in the`
  line `ordinary manner within the time that can be allowed for the execution of such work so as to`
  line `prevent such injury, the said officer may require any person named in such list to furnish as`
  line `many labourers (not exceeding the number which, according to the said list he is liable to`
  line `supply) as to the said officer seems necessary for the immediate execution of such work.`
  line
  line `Every requisition so made shall be in writing, and shall state--`
  line
  line `(a) the nature and locality of the work to be done;`
  line
  line `(b) the number of labourers to be supplied by the person upon whom the requisition is made ;`
  line and
  line
  line `(c) the approximate time for which and the day on which the labourers will be required;`
  line
  line `and a copy thereof shall be immediately sent to the Superintending Canal-officer for the`
  line `information of the State Government.`
  line
  line `The State Government shall fix, and may from time to time alter the rates to be paid to any such`
  line `labourers: Provided that such rates shall exceed the highest rates for the time being paid in the neighbourhood for similar work. In the case of every such labourer, the payment shall continue for the`
  line `whole period during which he is, in consequence of the provisions of this Part, prevented from`
  line `following his ordinary occupation.`
  line
  line `The State Government may ^1*** direct that the provisions of this Part shall apply, either`
  line `permanently or temporarily (as the case may be), to any district or part of a district for the`
  line `purpose of effecting necessary annual silt-clearances, or to prevent the proper operation of a`
  line `canal or drainage-work being stopped or so much interfered with as to stop the established`
  line `course of irrigation or drainage.`
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (46584)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Liability of labourers under requisition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46584&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `When any requisition has been made on any person`
  line `named in the said list, every labourer ordinarily resident within the village or estate of such person shall`
  line `be liable to supply, and to continue to supply, his labour, for the purposes aforesaid.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (46585)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Jurisdiction under this Act of Civil Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46585&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `Except where herein otherwise provided, all`
  line `claims against the State Government in respect of anything done under this Act may be tried by the Civil`
  line `Courts; but no such Court shall in any case pass an order as to the supply of canal-water to any crop sown`
  line `or growing at the time of such order.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (46586)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Settlement of differences as to mutual rights and liabilities of persons interested in water-course.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46586&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `Whenever a difference arises between two or more persons in regard to`
  line `their mutual rights or liabilities in respect of the use, construction or maintenance of a watercourse, any such person may apply in writing to the Divisional Canal-officer stating the`
  line `matter in dispute. Such officer shall thereupon give notice to the other persons interested that,`
  line `on a day to be named in such notice, he will proceed to inquire into the said matter. And, after`
  line `such inquiry, he shall pass his order thereon, unless he transfers (as he is hereby empowered`
  line `to do) the matter to the Collector, who shall thereupon inquire into and pass his order on the`
  line `said matter.`
  line
  line `Such order shall be final as to the use or distribution of water for any crop sown or growing`
  line `at the time when such order is made, and shall thereafter remain in force until set aside by the`
  line `decree of a Civil Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (46587)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Power to summon and examine witnesses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (Act 5 of 1908).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46587&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `Any officer empowered under this Act to`
  line `conduct any inquiry may exercise all such powers connected with the summoning and examining`
  line `of witnesses as are conferred on Civil Courts by the ^1Code of Civil Procedure, and every such`
  line `inquiry shall be deemed a judicial proceeding.`
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (46588)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Offences under Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46588&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, without proper authority and voluntarily, does any of the acts`
  line `following, that is to say:--`
  line
  line `(1) damages, alters, enlarges or obstructs any canal or drainage-work;`
  line
  line `(2) interferes with, increases or diminishes the supply of water in, or the flow of water from,`
  line `through, over or under, any canal or drainage-work;`
  line
  line `(3) interferes with or alters the flow of water in any river or stream, so as to endanger, damage`
  line `or render less useful any canal or drainage-work;`
  line
  line `(4) being responsible for the maintenance of a water-course, or using a water-course,`
  line `neglects to take proper precautions for the prevention of waste of the water thereof, or`
  line `interferes with the authorised distribution of the water therefrom, or uses such water in a n`
  line `unauthorised manner;`
  line
  line `(5) corrupts or fouls the water of any canal so as to render it less fit for the purposes for which`
  line `it is ordinarily used;`
  line
  line `(6) causes any vessel to enter or navigate any canal contrary to the rules for the time being`
  line `prescribed by the State Government for entering or navigating such canal;`
  line
  line `(7) while navigating on any canal, neglects to take proper precautions for the safety of the`
  line `canal and of vessels thereon;`
  line
  line `(8) being liable to furnish labourers under Part VIII of this Act, fails wi thout`
  line `reasonable cause, to supply or to assist in supplying the labourers required of him;`
  line
  line `(9) being a labourer liable to supply his labour under Part VIII of this Act, neglects, without`
  line `reasonable cause, so to supply, and to continue to supply, his labour;`
  line
  line `(10) destroys or moves any level-mark or water-gauge fixed by the authority of a public`
  line servant;
  line
  line `(11) passes, or causes animals or vehicles to pass, on or across any of the works,`
  line `banks or channels of a canal or drainage -work contrary to rules made under this Act,`
  line `after he has been desired to desist therefrom;`
  line
  line `(12) violates any rule made under this Act, for breach whereof a penalty may be`
  line incurred;
  line
  line `Penalty.--Shall be liable, on conviction before a Magistrate of such class as the State`
  line `Government directs in this behalf, to a fine not exceeding fifty rupees, or to imprisonment not`
  line `exceeding one month, or to both.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (46589)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Saving of prosecution under other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46589&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `Nothing herein contained shall prevent any person`
  line `from being prosecuted under any other law for any offence punishable under this Act: Provided that no`
  line `person shall be punished twice for the same offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (46590)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Compensation to person injured.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46590&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any person is fined for an offence under this Act,`
  line `the Magistrate may direct that the whole or any part of such fine may be paid by way of compensation to`
  line `the person injured by such offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (46591)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Power to arrest without warrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46591&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `Any person in charge of or employed upon any`
  line `canal or drainage-work may remove from the lands or buildings belonging thereto, or may take`
  line `into custody without a warrant and take forthwith before a Magistrate or to the nearest police -`
  line `station, to be dealt with according to law, any person who, within his view, commits any of the`
  line `following offences:--`
  line
  line `(1) wilfully damages or obstructs any canal or drainage work;`
  line
  line `(2) without proper authority interferes with the supply or flow of water in or from any`
  line `canal or drainage-work, or in any river or stream, so as to endanger, damage or render less`
  line `useful any canal or drainage-work.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (46592)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Definition of “canal”.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46592&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `In this Part the word "canal" shall (unless there be something`
  line `repugnant in the subject or context) be deemed to include also all lands occupied by the State`
  line `Government for the purposes of canals, and all buildings, machinery, fences, gates and other`
  line `erections, trees, crops, plantations or other produce occupied by or belonging to the State`
  line `Government upon such lands.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (46593)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Power to make, alter and cancel rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549&sectionId=46593&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00018_187308_1523269512549
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, from time to time`
  line `^1*** make rules to regulate the following matters:--`
  line
  line `(1) the proceedings of any officer who, under any provision of this Act, is required or`
  line `empowered to take action in any matter;`
  line
  line `(2) the cases in which, and the officers to whom, and the conditions subject to which,`
  line `orders and decisions, given under any provision of this Act, and not expressly provided for`
  line `as regards appeal, shall be appealable;`
  line
  line `(3) the persons by whom, ^2[and] the time, place or manner at or in which anything for the doing`
  line `of which provision is made under this Act, shall be done;`
  line
  line `(4) the amount of any charge made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(5) and generally to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `The State Government may from time to time ^3*** alter or cancel any rules so made.`
  line
  line `Publication of rules.--Such rules, alterations and cancelments shall be published in the Official`
  line `Gazette, and shall thereupon have the force of law.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 75 of Act VIII of 1873.— Section 75 of the principal Act shall be re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof, and the following shall be added as sub-sections (2) and (3) thereof ;`
  line
  line `“(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the powers contained under sub-section (1), the rules may provide for —`
  line
  line `(i) the particulars to be mentioned in the scheme repaired under this chapter ;`
  line
  line `(ii) the manner of implementation of the scheme ;`
  line
  line `(iii) the manner of publication of the scheme and giving or publishing of notice under this chapter ; and`
  line
  line `(iv) the manner of doing or execution of such other things as can be, or may be, prescribed for giving effect to the provisions of this chapter.`
  line
  line `(3) All rules made under this Act shall, as soon as may be after they are made, be laid before each House of the State Legislature while it is in session, for a total period of fourteen days extending in its one session or more than one successive sessions and shall, unless some later date is appointed, take effect, from the date of their publication in the Gazette, subject to such modifications or annulments as the two Houses of the Legislature may agree to make ; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done thereunder.”`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act V of 1963, s. 5]`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 75.—In section 75 of the principal Act, in sub-section (1), for clause (4), the following clause shall be substituted, namely :—`
  line
  line `“(4) the amount of any charges made under this Act and the manner in which they shall be realized ; and”`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 22 of 1979, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words subject to the control of the G. G. in C. omitted by Act 38 of 1920.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 12 of 1891.`
  line
  line `3. The words subject to the like control omitted by Act 38 of 1920.`
